# [CATS](../wg/cats.html)

## Summary

The Computing-Aware Traffic Steering (CATS) Working Group met at IETF 126 in Vienna. The session was chaired by Peng Liu and Adrian Farrel. The chairs provided status updates on active working group documents, highlighting that the CATS framework and use cases are currently in the RFC Editor Queue (RFC-Ed Queue), `draft-ietf-cats-metric-definition` is undergoing early review, and `draft-ietf-cats-oam-fw` has been newly adopted as a working group document. AD Jim Guichard recently approved new milestones, including those for a data model document, protocol applicability, and OAM. 

The meeting featured progress updates on both active working group drafts, followed by presentations of individual submissions covering protocol applicability, data models, BGP-LS metadata distribution, service-specific metrics, service platform definitions, midhaul and optical transport network (OTN) applicability, and operational metric semantics. A key recurring theme was the necessity of defining protocol requirements within the CATS working group before bringing specific protocol extensions to downstream working groups (such as IDR, PCE, and LSR).

