### 2. CATS Metrics Definition
* **Presenter**: Kehan Wang
* **Slides**: [2.1-cats-metrics-definition](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/126/materials/slides-126-cats-2a-cats-metrics-definition-00)
* **Draft**: `draft-ietf-cats-metric-definition`
* **Discussion**:
  * Kehan Wang summarized updates since IETF 125 (revisions -07 to -10), acknowledging feedback from Adrian Farrel (chair review), Jack Line (SEC early review), and early reviews from the OPS area.
  * Key updates include clarifying the distinct behaviors of **aggregation functions** (which combine homogeneous or heterogeneous inputs—defined as spatial, temporal, and cross-category aggregation) and **normalization functions** (which adjust a single input into a unitless, bounded score, such as via sigmoid or min-max scaling).
  * Level 1 metrics were renamed to "metrics combined in categories" to clarify that they may retain physical units or be unitless depending on the aggregation function used.
  * Security considerations were revised to address five key areas: integrity, authenticity, controllability, freshness, and confidentiality.
  * *Q&A*: Adrian Farrel asked if ideas from other metric-related drafts on the agenda should be merged or kept separate. Kehan Wang responded that ideas from those drafts would serve as valuable inputs for the operational and implementation considerations section.

