### 7. Computing Service Metric Definition and Operation
* **Presenter**: Lina Ji
* **Slides**: [3.4-draft-zhangb-cats-service-metrics-op](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/126/materials/slides-126-cats-34-draft-zhangb-cats-service-metrics-op-00)
* **Discussion**:
  * Lina Ji presented service-oriented metrics ("guess"—representing available concurrent capacity, and "computing time"—representing expected processing time) designed to bridge the gap between raw hardware metrics and the control plane.
  * *Q&A*:
    * Kehan Wang suggested integrating these metrics directly into the main `draft-ietf-cats-metric-definition` document (under operational considerations) rather than maintaining a separate draft. Lina Ji argued that this work is service-specific and should remain independent.
    * Susan Hares asked if the "computing time" metric assumes network-wide synchronization. Lina Ji clarified that computing time is derived locally by the service instance and reported as an elapsed delta, meaning global timestamp synchronization is not required.

