### 9. Compute-Aware Traffic Steering for Midhaul Networks
* **Presenter**: Luis M. Contreras
* **Slides**: [3.6-Compute-Aware Traffic Steering for Midhaul Networks](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/126/materials/slides-126-cats-36-compute-aware-traffic-steering-for-midhaul-networks-00)
* **Discussion**:
  * Luis M. Contreras explained how CATS can apply to ORAN midhaul networks to connect Distributed Units (DU) with Centralized Units (CU), focusing on the interface between the ORAN Service Management and Orchestrator (SMO) and CATS components.
  * *Q&A*:
    * Carlos J. Bernardos pointed out a potential relationship with DMM work on mobile traffic steering. Luis M. Contreras agreed to review it.
    * Adrian Farrel asked if this represented a layered or stitched architecture. Luis M. Contreras described it as more akin to stitching, where the transport network dynamically provides the requested connectivity to entities governed by the SMO.
    * Juan Deng asked if there were gaps in the existing CATS data model for this use case. Luis M. Contreras expressed interest in collaborating to map potential gaps into the data model draft.

