### 10. Computation-aware Traffic Steering in Optical Transport Networks (OTN)
* **Presenter**: OTN Presenter
* **Slides**: [3.7-Framework and Applicability of Computation-aware Traffic Steering in Optical Transport Networks](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/126/materials/slides-126-cats-framework-and-applicability-of-computation-aware-traffic-steering-in-optical-transport-networks-01)
* **Discussion**:
  * The presenter proposed utilizing OTN and Fine-Grain OTN (FG-OTN) as a deterministic, hard-isolated underlay option for CATS, particularly to connect distributed accelerator/GPU clusters. The proposed workflow covers matrix distribution, joint selection, and deterministic container encapsulation.
  * Next steps include aligning the analysis with official CATS use cases and performing a protocol gap analysis.

