### 11. Operational Semantics for CATS Metric Consumption
* **Presenter**: Longfei Xia
* **Slides**: [3.8-draft-zhu-cats-metric-semantics](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/126/materials/slides-126-cats-slides-126-cats-38-draft-zhu-cats-metric-semantics-00)
* **Discussion**:
  * Longfei Xia presented on the challenge of dealing with outdated metrics at the decision point. The draft proposes three operational semantics: freshness (temporal confidence), operational acceptability (what the consumer is allowed to do with the metric), and assurance exposure (operational visibility).
  * *Q&A*: Kehan Wang suggested integrating the freshness concept into `draft-ietf-cats-metric-definition` under the operational considerations section. Adrian Farrel supported the concepts introduced in the draft.

